=== cmd 0: [fork enter --help] ===
Enter fork mode for a network

Start a local Anvil fork of the specified network, backup registry files, and prepare the
environment for fork-mode testing.

The network's RPC endpoint in foundry.toml must use an environment variable (e.g.,
${SEPOLIA_RPC_URL}) so that treb can override it for the fork.

Usage: treb fork enter [OPTIONS] <NETWORK|--network <NETWORK>>

Arguments:
  [NETWORK]
          Network name or chain ID

Options:
      --network <NETWORK>
          Network name or chain ID

      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also respected via NO_COLOR env var)

      --non-interactive
          Skip interactive prompts (also enabled via TREB_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, CI=true, or non-TTY
          stdin/stdout)

      --rpc-url <RPC_URL>
          Explicit RPC URL (overrides network)
          
          [aliases: --url]

      --fork-block-number <FORK_BLOCK_NUMBER>
          Fork at a specific block number

      --json
          Output as JSON

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
